cs.CR, cs.GT, cs.SY, cs.NI, cs.AI 

The paper deals with cyber-security threats and utilizes game theory to develop defense strategies. This suggests that the paper could belong to the categories of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). Additionally, the paper also considers resource constraints and asymmetric feedback structures, which could fall under the categories of cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Finally, the paper uses algorithms to find optimal strategies, which could also place it under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
